<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Introduction"><span>Introduction&nb=
sp;</span></h1>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"12a262ae-6645-43f0-9741-257974d3fcf6"><span>Today<span st=
yle=3D"color:#172b4d;">&nbsp;services integrate with Adonis by enabling <a =
href=3D"https://confluence.eng.nutanix.com:8443/display/AI/Adonis+gRPC+Prox=
ying" rel=3D"nofollow">gRPC Proxying</a> between Adonis and a Backend gRPC =
Service.</span><span style=3D"color:#172b4d;"> This proxy accepts HTTP requ=
est, forwards it to the Backend Service via gRPC request, receive the gRPC =
response, and transform it to HTTP response</span></span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"6fa05e24-dc2f-469d-833b-e0cc5bd0fec2"><span>There is alre=
ady support for <a href=3D"https://confluence.eng.nutanix.com:8443/pages/vi=
ewpage.action?spaceKey=3DAI&amp;title=3DWrite+a+File+Download+API+in+Adonis=
" rel=3D"nofollow">download and upload API</a></span><span> that downloads/=
uploads the file on/from the client side by calling the v4 API for the adon=
is residing controllers</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"1a9c0bbf-ba31-499b-b614-06d872318539"><span>The current f=
ile upload/download API support is not present for gRPC path in Adonis</spa=
n></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"2dc49f7e-6b30-4d11-971e-91dffd1ef962"><span>For sizes gre=
ater than 1GB refer&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.eng.nutanix.com:8443=
/x/6SnBEg" rel=3D"nofollow">objects lite solution</a></span></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Goals"><span>Goals</span></h1>
<p><strong>Functional Goals</strong><span>&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"03f186ff-9a14-4da0-9cae-c5fe196dc177">Clients need the ab=
ility to either download files locally or upload files upto 1GB to and from=
 the gRPC backend service by invoking the v4 API</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"5d75fc85-a17d-4331-b17b-3ddac8217443">Enable streaming su=
pport for large file upload and download regardless of the file format</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"7a92cd3d-8915-4401-99d5-9278dfa82331">Generate Protos, DT=
Os, mappers, controller, service, service implementation using gRPC client =
stub to interact with backend service for controller teams by just defining=
 the YAMLs</li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Non-FunctionalGoals">Non-Functional=
 Goals</h4>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"f4fb619e-3708-4dff-a293-9376f6ba29a6">File upload/downloa=
d API needs to be highly performant, reliable</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"2a6feebf-bad4-4e90-b0d6-ae19a5bbc271">File streaming shou=
ld not overwhelm Adonis or the backend gRPC service's memory</li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Non-Goals">Non-Goals</h4>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"827e7df8-aeb2-4ea1-ac50-77b72c1163dd"><span>Support resum=
e upload/download is not planned for first phase</span></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Terminology">Terminology</h1>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"6140d1ea-21e1-4807-9a8e-b41d2e9cebe7">gRPC=20
  <ul>
   <li>It is a high-performance, open-source RPC (Remote Procedure Call) fr=
amework developed by Google, designed for efficient communication between d=
istributed systems</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"8cf0afaa-a6f1-4a45-9766-6d058ba6ff77">Streaming RPC=20
  <ul>
   <li data-uuid=3D"5fed1c9e-1d3f-4e70-a0c8-90ca49840c4e">Streaming RPCs al=
low you to asynchronously send and receive large data sets or real-time upd=
ates without blocking or buffering.</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"5cd25960-5710-474c-bc35-0be13c22ec0a">gRPC Metadata=20
  <ul>
   <li>It provides additional contextual information(key-value pair) that a=
ccompany gRPC messages, facilitating communication between clients and serv=
ers</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"a3b54dd8-8a9b-4d29-985c-e74db5a4e07e">Flow control=20
  <ul>
   <li>Is a mechanism used to manage the rate of data transmission between =
communicating entities, preventing one side from overwhelming the other wit=
h data and ensuring efficient communication</li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Requirements"><span>Requirements</s=
pan></h1>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"49ffb74e-4c6e-4db6-a28f-d4600851742a">Clients need the ab=
ility to either download files locally or upload files to and from the gRPC=
 backend service by invoking the v4 API</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"80f0b36b-f2e4-4eae-b2e5-2a8d13c2f382">In Adonis, we need =
support for file streaming in the gRPC path for backend services</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"468d9643-06d8-4893-985b-30f1deeeaaf6">The client can be e=
ither SDK-based/UI/CLI, while the backend service is a gRPC service</li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"3b527964-ff91-4c61-a25a-983564ff10d6"><span>The REST API =
produces and consumes application/octet-stream, application/pdf, applicatio=
n/zip</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"3e2bcce0-09ae-4f84-9410-73a18e4c8744"><span style=3D"lett=
er-spacing: 0.0px;">Consider flow control/back-pressure mechanisms as a mea=
ns of safeguarding endpoints and enhancing Adonis resilience</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"cc0e88d5-7a69-4dca-9798-3050b08d4f28"><span style=3D"lett=
er-spacing: 0.0px;">Adonis side controller methods in java and gRPC client =
stubs should be auto-generated whereas gRPC backend server can be in any la=
nguage</span></li>
</ul>
