<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Design"><span>Design</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Highlevelarchitecture"><span>High l=
evel architecture</span></h2>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &n=
bsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <span class=3D"conflu=
ence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"c=
onfluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=3D"468" src=3D"456e4bb8=
a0a4b6306690ad32bdaf98811ce9f22021e57db025c7c7a73592b0d9" data-image-src=3D=
"/download/attachments/308316663/image-2025-11-19_12-13-39.png?version=3D1&=
amp;modificationDate=3D1763534562596&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-=
count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"487362732" data-linked-resource-vers=
ion=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-def=
ault-alias=3D"image-2025-11-19_12-13-39.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confl=
uence.eng.nutanix.com:8443" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png"=
 data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"308316663" data-linked-resource-conta=
iner-version=3D"72" tabindex=3D"0" alt=3D"" height=3D"102"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span>When a client uploads/downloads a file to Adonis using an octet st=
ream, Adonis employs a <strong>gRPC channel</strong> using <strong>GRPC cli=
ent stub</strong> to stream the contents of the file to and from the <stron=
g>backend gRPC server</strong>.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><span>Adonis will generate contro=
llers which does conversion from HTTP =E2=86=94 proto and uses/has gRPC cli=
ent stubs to invoke the RPC hosted in gRPC backend service.</span></span></=
p>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><span>The file can be a resource(=
has an extId) or a non-resource to the backend gRPC Service.</span><br></sp=
an></p>
<p><strong style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">File Upload&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Client (POST) ----&gt; &nbsp; <span style=3D"color:#=
c25100;">Adonis</span> &nbsp;----&gt; <span style=3D"color:#c25100;">Servle=
ts InputStream</span> ----&gt; <span style=3D"color:#c25100;">gRPCStream</s=
pan> ----&gt; gRPC Backend Service</p>
<p><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;When a client uploads a file to Adonis using a=
n octet stream, Adonis reads file contents from servlets i/p stream and </s=
pan><span>invokes <strong>client streaming</strong> file upload RPC on the =
channel in order to <strong>stream</strong> the contents of the file to the=
 backend gRPC server.</span></p>
<p><strong>File Download</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Client&nbsp; (GET) &lt;---- <span style=3D"color:#c2=
5100;">Servlets O/p stream </span>&lt;----&nbsp; <span style=3D"color:#c251=
00;">Adonis</span> &nbsp;&lt;---- <span style=3D"color:#c25100;">gRPCStream=
</span> &lt;---- gRPC Backend Service</p>
<p><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;When a client requests to download a file from=
 Adonis using an octet stream, Adonis invokes <strong>server streaming </st=
rong>file download RPC in order to <strong>stream</strong> the contents of =
the file from the backend gRPC server and write to <strong>servlets o/p str=
eam asynchronously</strong>.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Since the file is processed as a stream of bytes, it remains agnostic to=
 the file format.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">To allow client/server to get file metadata(=
fileName, type), set file metadata on the gRPC <a href=3D"https://grpc.io/d=
ocs/guides/metadata/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">metadata</a>=
(key-value pair) which is sent with initial or final gRPC requests or respo=
nses.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span>Adonis needs to consider <strong>flow =
control/back-pressure</strong> mechanisms as a means of safeguarding endpoi=
nts and enhancing Adonis resilience. Implementation details in below sectio=
n.</span></p>
<p><span>The RPCs to use <strong>non-blocking/asynchronous </strong>stub th=
at makes non-blocking calls to the backend service, where the file upload/d=
ownload in Adonis is done asynchronously(w/o blocking servlet thread).</spa=
n></p>
<h2 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-APIDesign">API Design</h2>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"297cc723-c91b-4bcb-982d-5b35119fb1ed"><span>File download=
&nbsp;</span>
  <ul>
   <li><span>/files/{extId}</span>
    <ul>
     <li data-uuid=3D"768d1f91-3fec-4a5d-87e6-77512173c447"><span>name/extI=
d as request param (only for resource)</span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span>Get Request</span></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"85478df4-fb37-4ae4-962d-d07807476e02"><span>Supports cu=
stom query parameters</span></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"044d0c23-8f36-4320-a0fb-60903669da5c"><span>Produces</s=
pan>
    <ul>
     <li data-uuid=3D"fabc0bbe-64db-4749-a014-c6531e2ab1f2"><span>applicati=
on/octet-stream, application/pdf, application/zip</span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span>Response</span>
    <ul>
     <li><span>binary stream in response body&nbsp;</span></li>
     <li data-uuid=3D"8e23634a-58b1-489e-916c-3bbb831792a6"><span>200 Succe=
ss</span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span>Headers sent from adonis to backend server:</span>
    <ul>
     <li><span>File-Identifier (</span><span>name/id</span><span>) (only fo=
r resource)</span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span>Headers sent by backend server to adonis:</span><br>
    <ul>
     <li>File-Content-Length</li>
     <li><span>File-Content-Disposition</span></li>
     <li data-uuid=3D"759dff2a-86a2-472e-b62e-66d45d529e35"><span>Checksum =
(Optional)</span></li>
    </ul></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"30817775-0d04-43b1-84c8-dce04c95cfa9"><span>File upload:<=
/span>
  <ul>
   <li><span>/files</span></li>
   <li><span>Post Request</span>
    <ul>
     <li><span>binary stream in request body</span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"f5f8b56b-0ef6-44d6-92c9-523a76b598d5"><span>Consumes</s=
pan>
    <ul>
     <li data-uuid=3D"f03967a6-63b9-4de6-9215-7ba883c01662"><span>applicati=
on/octet-stream, application/pdf, application/zip</span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span>Response</span>
    <ul>
     <li><span>201 Success/500 Error</span></li>
     <li data-uuid=3D"7c0735d1-6527-48e5-a6c4-f69572eb86e8"><span><span sty=
le=3D"color:#333333;">ExtId of the resource created (only for resource)<br>=
</span></span></li>
     <li data-uuid=3D"41446e4e-2d0f-4bba-8248-74d1ca66798b"><span><span sty=
le=3D"color:#333333;">Location URL header of newly created resource</span><=
/span></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span>Headers forwarded from adonis to backend server:</span>
    <ul>
     <li><span>File-Identifier (</span><span>name/id</span><span>) (only fo=
r resource)</span></li>
     <li>File-Content-Length</li>
     <li><span>File-Content-Disposition</span></li>
     <li data-uuid=3D"53764042-5d40-4848-a7f8-a94275d70d76"><span>Checksum =
(Optional)</span></li>
    </ul></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<p><span><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbs=
p; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(These h<span style=3D"color:#333333;">eaders=
 are suppose to be sent by client in request</span>)</span></span></p>
<ul>
 <li style=3D"list-style-type: none;">
  <ul>
   <li><span>Headers sent by backend server to adonis: NA</span></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-DetailedImplementation">Detailed Im=
plementation</h2>
<h3 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Flowcontrol"><span>Flow control</sp=
an></h3>
<p><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Using gRPC's built in <a =
href=3D"https://grpc.io/docs/guides/flow-control/" class=3D"external-link" =
rel=3D"nofollow">flow control</a> with following configuration for flow par=
ameters:</span>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
 <li style=3D"list-style-type: none;" data-uuid=3D"d10655f9-71ab-4c96-b915-=
95aee972c1cb">
  <ul>
   <li><span>gRPC flow control is by default enabled in go, python but exce=
ptionally in java &amp; C</span></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"8e12b3a5-2e96-4657-9ca5-0cbfadd7e03f">
    <p class=3D"p1"><span class=3D"s1">Java has protection for receiver by =
default in and protection for sender is opt in</span></p></li>
   <li><span>gRPCs by default inbound message size is 4MB</span></li>
   <li><span>Adonis (Java)</span>&nbsp;=20
    <ul>
     <li>
      <p><u>Inbound traffic</u>:</p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <p>Automatic flow control</p></li>
       <li>Won't request next message until existing one is consumed</li>
       <li>maxInboundMessageSize : 4MB (by default)</li>
      </ul></li>
     <li>
      <p><u>Outbound traffic:</u></p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <p>Not automatic flow control</p></li>
       <li><span>to avoid <span style=3D"color:#333333;">excessive bufferin=
g per stream within client</span> check if client is ready to send message&=
nbsp;</span></li>
       <li>
        <p>maxOutBoundMessageSize : 4MB</p></li>
      </ul></li>
    </ul></li>
   <li><span><span style=3D"color:#333333;">GRPC backend service (Any langu=
age)</span></span>
    <ul>
     <li><span><span style=3D"color:#333333;"> flow control up-to client</s=
pan></span></li>
     <li>maxInboundMessageSize : same as Adonis's maxOutBoundMessageSize</l=
i>
     <li>maxOutBoundMessageSize : same as Adonis's maxInboundMessageSize</l=
i>
    </ul></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-StreamObserver"><strong>Stream Obse=
rver</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"3102932a-7768-4828-9f57-907084ecc36a"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Base interface for handling streaming RPCs (client or server)=
.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"665ff256-91ea-432d-a87b-7141f8aa7840"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Core interface in gRPC Java for receiving stream events.</spa=
n></li>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"e786cb6a-b29d-4c9c-b8ad-d5ddb04da309"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Implemented on both client and server sides and used in all s=
treaming RPC types.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"ba046163-2cd8-40ab-a259-50e506f1a08c"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Used when no flow control is required</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"5db7b9c7-73eb-47ad-aef1-f8cdc5eb23a6"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Methods:</span>
  <ul>
   <li data-uuid=3D"fa01002f-ed40-45c1-a819-398ef87a0900">onNext(T value) =
=E2=86=92 handle incoming message</li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"3b895b16-ed77-4a76-9da3-62cc09377a16">onError(Throwable=
 t) =E2=86=92 handle error</li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"e59cb927-e551-4778-8e56-eb0679a92614">onCompleted() =E2=
=86=92 handle stream completion</li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;"><strong><span>CallStreamObserver</span></=
strong></p>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"8d93142f-b4ef-43f4-8e62-1b08e5d2f911"><span class=3D"s1">=
Extension of StreamObserver with extra control (flow control, readiness sig=
nals).</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"aaeeca9a-2b42-4e28-b918-beade5442d97"><span class=3D"s1">=
Methods:&nbsp; </span>
  <ul>
   <li data-uuid=3D"ece4fcfd-c469-4b8f-912c-0a3c99466b83"><span class=3D"s1=
">isReady() =E2=86=92 check if the observer can accept more messages.</span=
></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"c241fc0c-f196-4645-b8ec-30af69f7ca7f"><span class=3D"s1=
">setOnReadyHandler(Runnable) =E2=86=92 callback when ready to send more.</=
span></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"2305d612-01fc-448b-93b5-460616465281"><span class=3D"s1=
">disableAutoInboundFlowControl() =E2=86=92 manually control inbound flow.<=
/span></li>
   <li data-uuid=3D"a9c9420d-0a80-400e-88aa-c6e9c9db9cf6"><span class=3D"s1=
">request(int count) =E2=86=92 pull-based flow control.</span></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>ClientCallStreamO=
bserver</strong></span></p>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"4c79da3c-5be2-4781-889d-8858d0090ce1"><span class=3D"s1">=
Client-side specialization of CallStreamObserver for lower-level client cal=
l control.</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"cd792d71-d941-4dca-8e9c-5d24e6047edb"><span class=3D"s1">=
Adds client-specific controls (e.g., canceling calls, setting message compr=
ession).</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"16ff1e33-51a0-49fb-bada-6f9225d8259b"><span class=3D"s1">=
Obtained via casting the StreamObserver returned by a stub or via ClientRes=
ponseObserver.</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"edfa5d23-ba9b-4880-945b-f763a9de3fec"><span class=3D"s1">=
Used when the client needs low-level control over outgoing requests.</span>=
</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-OtherConfigurations"><span>Other Co=
nfigurations</span></h3>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"c62a2438-ddc4-4c9b-8083-ed0b9dbfb258"><span>Size limit : =
1 GB (413 Request Entity Too Large If file size more than this)</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"18ce8638-cffe-4b2f-a503-022f06e36e63"><span>Byte array si=
ze is 4MB and configurable in Adonis</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"90a0ef46-9ff5-4088-88b9-edb41e994f62"><span>File location=
 : Can be present on any local storage on PC/PE/SMSP</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"fd09b9c2-9edd-4ff0-968a-116ba9e7ff6f"><span>Message compr=
ession : No&nbsp;</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"95209735-c767-4369-808b-681ed8b609b5"><span>Security : P<=
/span><span>laintext</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"16d85156-bdfc-4eb6-88d4-6c7ce64a95f0"><span>Rate limit : =
Add API rate limit max of 2-5/second. SLA rps (Lower due to resource use)</=
span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"0e12010a-c54c-4ba1-b6f2-55e5ed0e99ea"><span>Error handlin=
g :&nbsp;</span>
  <ul>
   <li><span>graceful handle the error while failure of upload/download of =
file request</span></li>
  </ul></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"a23a99d6-f5f3-4d44-b3b2-ff6794e3fdd9"><span>Timeouts:&nbs=
p;</span>
  <ul>
   <li><span>what happens in network issues? : Configure timeout of 30 secs=
</span></li>
  </ul></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"91a6d748-14c1-474c-9097-028d2a681a22"><span>Concurrency:<=
/span>
  <ul>
   <li><span>multiple file upload and download support</span></li>
   <li><span>we require rate limiter to control concurrent requests</span><=
/li>
  </ul></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"63f2a17d-f446-4112-bccf-977bc4c44111"><span>Supported fil=
e formats</span>
  <ul>
   <li><span>txt, image, tar, zip, etc</span></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li data-uuid=3D"2e8e73ec-9aef-4b98-984b-00b52fa7c7c7"><span>Circuit break=
er : To be enabled in <span style=3D"color:#172b4d;">gRPC based controllers=
</span></span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"5a73f0e0-b416-485a-8fb6-5005366d2cb8"><span>Documentation=
 changes : Already supported</span></li>
 <li data-uuid=3D"5bf1326d-d920-48a6-ab16-eaf762d1b989"><span>SDK changes :=
 Already supported</span></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-StreamingResponseBody"><span>Stream=
ingResponseBody&nbsp;</span></h3>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 40.0px;"><span>Spring provides&nbsp;</span><span>S=
treamingResponseBody :</span><span>A controller method=E2=80=99s return val=
ue type for asynchronous request processing allows the application to write=
 directly to the response OutputStream without blocking the servlet contain=
er thread.</span><span>The type</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"col=
or:#5d1f1a;">StreamingResponseBody</span><span>&nbsp;represents a special k=
ind of response body. The idea is, instead of having the large file data st=
ick in a HTTP response, we want to return a streaming object so that the cl=
ient end can use the stream object to fetch the data back.</span></p>
<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-SampleImplementation"><span>Sample =
Implementation</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-Servicedefinition"><span>Service de=
finition</span></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
 <div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px;">
  <b class=3D"code-title">File Service Proto</b><span class=3D"collapse-sou=
rce expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-i=
con icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
 </div>
 <div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
  <pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"bru=
sh: java; gutter: false; collapse: true">syntax =3D "proto3";
option java_multiple_files =3D true;

service FileService{
  rpc downloadFile (DownloadArg) returns (stream Data);
  rpc uploadFile(stream UploadArg) returns(UploadRet);
}

message DownloadArg {}

message Data{
  bytes data =3D 1;
}

message UploadArg {
=09
}

message Data{
  bytes data =3D 1;
}

message UploadRet {
  /*
   * field containing expected response content
   */
 &nbsp;platform.v4.config.UploadApiResponse content =3D 999;
}

message UploadApiResponse {
  oneof data {
    platform.v4.config.StringWrapper string_data =3D 2080;

    platform.config.ErrorResponseWrapper error_response_data =3D 400;
  }
 &nbsp;platform.common.v1.response.ApiResponseMetadata metadata =3D 1001;
}</pre>
 </div>
</div>
