<h3 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-AdonisRestController.1"><strong cla=
ss=3D"code-title">Adonis Rest Controller</strong></h3>
<p><span class=3D"code-title">Spring provides <a href=3D"https://docs.sprin=
g.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/web/serv=
let/mvc/method/annotation/StreamingResponseBody.html" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">StreamingResponseBody</a> : A controller method=E2=80=
=99s return value type for asynchronous request processing allows the appli=
cation to write directly to the response OutputStream without blocking the =
servlet container thread.</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
 <div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px;">
  <b class=3D"code-title">Download controller block</b><span class=3D"colla=
pse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-co=
ntrol-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand so=
urce</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
 </div>
 <div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
  <pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"bru=
sh: java; gutter: false; collapse: true">@RequestMapping(value =3D "/files/=
{extId}", produces =3D MediaType.APPLICATION_OCTET_STREAM_VALUE, method =3D=
 RequestMethod.GET)
public ResponseEntity&lt;StreamingResponseBody&gt; downloadFile(@PathVariab=
le(required =3D true) String extId,
                                                      HttpServletRequest re=
quest,
                                                      HttpServletResponse r=
esponse) {

    StreamingResponseBody stream =3D out -&gt; {

      CompletableFuture&lt;Void&gt; completable =3D new CompletableFuture&l=
t;&gt;();

      StreamObserver&lt;Data&gt; streamObserver =3D new StreamObserver&lt;D=
ata&gt;() {
        @Override
        public void onNext(Data data) {
          try {
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;// TODO : Set Content-Length and =
Content-Disposition as response headers if not set
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;out.write(data.getData().toByteAr=
ray());
            out.flush();
          } catch (Exception e) {
            log.error("error on write to byte array stream", e);
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;requestStream.cancel(msg, e);
            completable.completeExceptionally(e);
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }
        }

        @Override
        public void onError(Throwable t) {
          log.error("error occurred while downloading file ", t);
          completable.completeExceptionally(t);
        }

        @Override
        public void onCompleted() {
          log.info("File download request has been completed!");
          completable.complete(null);
        }
      };

      try {
        log.info("Downloading file...");
        // TODO : Set grpc metadata like extId, on the HeaderInterceptor
        fileServiceStub.downloadFile(DownloadFileParams.newBuilder().build(=
), streamObserver);
        // blocks the async thread until the file download is complete
        completable.get(3, TimeUnit.MINUTES);
      } catch (Exception e) {
        log.error("Error occurred while creating the download request");
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;HttpHeaders httpHeaders =3D new HttpHeaders();
        httpHeaders.setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);
        throw new DownloadFailed(message, httpHeaders, null, null);
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }
    };

    // Return the ResponseEntity with the StreamingResponseBody and headers
    return  ResponseEntity.ok().contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_OCTET_STR=
EAM)
                                    .body(stream);
}</pre>
 </div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-gRPCService"><strong class=3D"code-=
title">gRPC Service</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
 <div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px;">
  <b class=3D"code-title">download sample gRPC service</b><span class=3D"co=
llapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand=
-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand=
 source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
 </div>
 <div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
  <pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"bru=
sh: java; gutter: false; collapse: true"> &nbsp;private static final Metada=
ta.Key&lt;String&gt; CONTENT_LENGTH =3D
      Metadata.Key.of("Content-Length", Metadata.ASCII_STRING_MARSHALLER);

  private static final Metadata.Key&lt;String&gt; CONTENT_DISPOSITION =3D
      Metadata.Key.of("Content-Disposition", Metadata.ASCII_STRING_MARSHALL=
ER);

  private final Metadata.Key&lt;String&gt; FILE_IDENTIFIER =3D
          Metadata.Key.of("File-Identifier", Metadata.ASCII_STRING_MARSHALL=
ER);
 &nbsp;
  private final int BYTE_ARRAY_SIZE =3D 4 * 1024 * 1024;

  /**
   * Implement as per your service where onNext method will read file and w=
rite data to observer while onError and complete methods
   * send error or success response as per the operation.
   */
  public void downloadFile(DownloadFileParams request, StreamObserver&lt;Da=
ta&gt; responseObserver) {
    // TODO : Get extId from header interceptor
    String extId =3D HeaderServerInterceptor.getReceivedHeaders().get(FILE_=
IDENTIFIER); &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
    assert extId !=3D null; &nbsp;=20
    log.info("Request to download file");

    // read the file and convert to a byte array
    String filePath =3D Paths.get(ABS_PATH).toAbsolutePath().resolve(Paths.=
get(extId)).toString();

    final ServerCallStreamObserver&lt;Data&gt; serverCallStreamObserver =3D
        (ServerCallStreamObserver&lt;Data&gt;) responseObserver;

    // Set up a back-pressure-aware consumer for the request stream. The on=
ReadyHandler will be invoked
    // when the consuming side has enough buffer space to receive more mess=
ages.
 &nbsp; &nbsp;//On server-side it may only be called during the initial cal=
l to the application, before the service returns its StreamObserver.
    class OnReadyHandler implements Runnable {
      FileInputStream fis =3D null;
      final byte[] buffer =3D new byte[BYTE_ARRAY_SIZE];
      int read =3D 0;
      public OnReadyHandler() {
        try {
          fis =3D new FileInputStream(filePath);
        }
        catch (Exception e) {
          closeStream(fis);
          String msg =3D "Unable to read the file {}";
          log.error(msg, e.toString());
          serverCallStreamObserver.onError(io.grpc.Status.ABORTED.withDescr=
iption(msg + filePath).withCause(e).asException());
        }
      }

      @Override
      public void run() {
        try { &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;=20
          while (serverCallStreamObserver.isReady()) {
          if ((read =3D fis.read(buffer)) &gt; 0) {
            serverCallStreamObserver.onNext(Data.newBuilder().setData(
                                                    ByteString.copyFrom(buf=
fer, 0, read)).build());
          }
          else {
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; closeStream(fis);
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; serverCallStreamObserver.onCompl=
eted();
             log.info("Completed file download request");
           =20
          }
         }
        }
          catch (Exception e) {
            closeStream(fis);
            serverCallStreamObserver.onError(io.grpc.Status.ABORTED.withDes=
cription("Unable to read the " +
                                                                           =
 "file " + filePath).withCause(e).asException());
          }
      }
    } &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
     =20
      final OnReadyHandler onReadyHandler =3D new OnReadyHandler();
      serverCallStreamObserver.setOnReadyHandler(onReadyHandler);
      serverCallStreamObserver.setOnCancelHandler(() -&gt; {
        log.info("Client cancelled the request");
        closeStream(onReadyHandler.fis);
      }); &nbsp;=20
   }

 &nbsp;  private void closeStream(java.io.Closeable closeable) {
      try {
        if (closeable !=3D null) {
          log.info("Closing stream....");
          closeable.close();
        }
      }
      catch (Exception e) {
        log.error(e.toString());
      }
    }</pre>
 </div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"v4APIsgRPCFileTransfersupport-BestPracticesforClients"><span>Best=
 Practices for Clients</span></h1>
<p><span><span style=3D"color:#172b4d;">Refer the client usage references g=
iven above or check references section for client reference integrations.</=
span></span></p>
<ul>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"4655df54-4e3f-4649-8aad-116e3407c3c1"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Define all file transfer APIs in accordance with established =
standards and submit them for review to #v4-api-review-board.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li1" data-uuid=3D"295ee0eb-fdc4-4980-b44e-650fcf04116c"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Please follow API schema in API Design section for input and =
output</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"c37e6b1b-b776-44a4-9db1-3857683b8f65"><span=
 class=3D"s1">For uploads, include a checksum header to validate API integr=
ity; for downloads, ensure the checksum is returned as a header.</span></li=
>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"6459642f-e941-40b2-8a83-a85f24f4edf2"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Adonis can connect either to a local backend or one of the th=
ree deployed backend services in a scaled setup, depending on the </span><s=
pan class=3D"s2">gRPC serviceInfo</span><span class=3D"s1"> configuration.<=
/span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"378118cb-c6eb-43a7-9778-0b50f2f4fb38"><span=
 class=3D"s1">In scaled deployments, if files must be available across all =
PC nodes, use shared storage for consistent read/write access.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"91161797-c326-44e4-8f0c-c902c6847aeb"><span=
 class=3D"s1">When the backend service is implemented in Java or Python, en=
sure proper flow control for outbound traffic.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"d8dcd5a8-1f2b-4dd9-a15f-c2692c2d8316"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Always return a clear error response with the appropriate err=
or message in case of failures.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"0647b914-8525-4da2-94c0-27b04c1db227"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Use the latest dev platform at all times.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"60687313-acdf-4942-8680-e3b00e42cd6f"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Add an error listener and log events for debugging whenever e=
rrors or exceptions are sent to or received from Adonis.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"d2a11747-5db6-4e87-a1a1-538b60a802e5"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Log all headers received or published on the gRPC server.</sp=
an></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"eedf98aa-a173-44f6-8203-61b4d037522a"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Conduct FMEA to assess risks if Adonis goes down or the conne=
ction breaks.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"185ca864-cc82-4976-b480-327c9d93b0f2"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Follow the configuration and flow control parameters outlined=
 in the Configuration section above.</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"6c4940db-b4c6-4f4b-b7cf-030704f4ab8a"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Add API Level rate limits for these APIs</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li2" data-uuid=3D"7977a90c-37c7-4743-a0a0-5b4ce3644f4d"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Close the connection/file stream after the file writing is co=
mplete</span></li>
 <li class=3D"li3" data-uuid=3D"610c5fb6-4a1f-414e-a134-7d103438d8e5"><span=
 class=3D"s1">Perform performance and memory profiling of backend gRPC serv=
er APIs and maintain the results as a benchmark.</span></li>
</ul>
